< text>
Eating here while traveling on an 18 hour drive was the best choice of the trip. The two gentlemen work were cheerful and helpful. My wife and be indecisive and he helped her get everything she wanted by putting items on the side and offering samples. We were the only ones in the restaurant for a short time and the two staff were talking to each other and seemed to genuinely be enjoyable people. The food was good. We had teriyaki, spicy chicken, and orange chicken. All was well cooked and tasted good. Environment, staff, and food made for an awesome afternoon stop.<//text>

< Text>
I go here every so often but as far as Chicken Bowls go, it's far from the best I've had. If you're in the area though and want something healthy like a Chicken Bowl then it's not terrible.

My biggest complaint is the Chicken itself, it's completely overcooked and tough/rubbery and while your choice of sauce covers up some of the dryness of the chicken, you definitely still notice how tough and overcooked it is, the flavor is fine though. Pricing is average, $8-$10 and portion size is good, I usually get the regular size and it's enough to fill me up.

Edit: In response to the owners response:

I just got the regular Spicy Chicken Bowl, I didn't specify chicken breast option but I'm pretty sure I had breast meat, not difficult to discern white meat from dark especially in texture.

I appreciate the response, I'll mention it to the manager next time I'm in about my experience.<//Text>

<rating>5< /rating>< Review>
We decided to come here halfway through a long drive. We weren't sure what to expect since there's not one of these close to San Diego, but we popped in just hoping for some decent grub to refuel ourselves. We were pleasantly surprised! The ability to customize your bowl was a welcomed one as was the variety of meats that were offered! Our table tried the crab rangoons, orange chicken, chicken katsu and teriyaki salmon. All of it was very tasty and fresh! It was obvious that it had all been cooked to order. This is a trip that we will be making fairly frequently and I have a feeling this will be a stopping point on every one.</Review>

<Review>From the feeling I get, everybody here is here not just to sell product, but to sincerely listen to you, and give you a true appraisal of what they see your needs are, and dispense whatever they feel is appropriate. They are not there just to sell you some product and quickly move on the the next customer. On my 1st visit, I worked with Autumn, who was SO patient, so full of information and personalized advice, and showed sincere interest in my personal needs. Combining those attributes with her obviously  well-developed extensive knowledge, made it such a positive experience. Autumn advised me---because this would be my 1st experience with cannabis, to start conservatively. We decided to see how it worked out and take it from there. I am so glad I waited while she finished her lunch break! This was at the end of December.
Today, Jan. 28, I was help by Nicole. First of all, she is such a nice person, and is also there to listen to me tell her what I was there hope that a cannabis product could do for me. <review>A little long but worth the read.

In the past I would have given this dispensary a 4 star but the most recent experience has lost me as a long time customer.

I purchased a $50 bottle of CBD tincture only to have the plunger malfunction a couple weeks after I purchased it. It happened while the bottle was packed in a hygiene bag during travel and the entire remaining contents, about 80%, leaked out. The plunger portion on the cap came out of its grooves that hold it in place. I used the product just fine for the 2 weeks before so it just wasn‚Äôt designed well enough to handle being packed for travel. I‚Äôve had plenty of success with other manufacturers packaging. This item was made by Care by Design and I will not be using them again.

I returned it to the store to show them and I expected a replacement and even offered to pay for the 20% that was used. They refused for the moment until they could contact the manufacturer. Three weeks later and still no follow up from them so I stopped by and left my number again and a follow up with one of the employees. A week later now and still nothing. No follow up or anything. I even have a history in their computer of long time customer loyalty but that didn‚Äôt make a bit of difference. Even told them this incident will determine if I continue to be a customer there and still nothing. I expected more from this establishment.

CBD has only medicinal value, no high, so it boggles my mind that they have sub par customer service in a medical industry. <resp>None<//resp>< Review>
Out of Stock is a phenomenon we probably all have experienced sometime in the course of our lives and it is never a pleasant incident; it is even less so for those responsible for it.

Retailers and manufacturers suffer huge losses every year because of empty shelves and disappointed customers. Damaged reputation and customer loyalty, decreased impact of promotions, and higher costs for re-ordering all multiply to millions, if not billions, of dollars lost.

But also late deliveries, under ordering, and not having clear responsibilities for inventory lead to empty shelves fairly quickly.

In order to really tackle the problem it is, therefore, essential for retailers and suppliers to coordinate their procedures and information sharing.  The Wellness Earth Energy Dispensary has major issues keeping RSO or Rick Simpson Oil product on shelves. Unfortunately, sick people cannot afford to have an unreliable retailer, especially with their medicine. Hopefully, their management team realizes the customers that they are losing and corrects this ineptitude moving forward.</Review>

< Review>
This place has a good selection of quality flower and edibles, but what stands out is the insane selection of concentrates‚Äîincluding some good and inexpensive shatter and sugar wax made locally and cut right off a sheet or scooped out of a tub by weigh.

There's a small parking lot, which The W.E.E.D. shares with a crossfit gym and Vendome Liquors but there's now free valet, so it's not usually an issue. The place has a pretty hip decor with lots of framed Shepard Fairey prints on the walls. Waiting room is spacious with plenty of seating, some T-shirts for sale, and an ATM. I've sometimes had to wait but never for very long. First-time patients register on a computer in the waiting area.

Always a handful of knowledgeable budtenders working at any given time and they're good about letting customers know about deals and specials.<//Review>

<pics>None< /pics><review>I must say, i have had good experiences while purchasing a few things in the past, id really only purchase an or two items at a time. Prices always seemed fair, especially for a small shop like this. However, last time I went in I was on the lookout for several spices to make Masala Chai. Always as helpful, i was led around the shop picking what i need which was great. They showed me my options when they had them and gave me recommendations. When i was finally done they gave me a quick rundown on how to make the Chai as i am a total noob to any of this and finally rang me up.  When i saw the register ring up $81.93 ( which was directly inputted at the register, like if he had been adding up the prices as we were picking the spices, just thought ok he's good with numbers), for some spices and some black tea I was in disbelief. My ignorance coupled with disbelief led me to just pay the bill and walk out the door scratching my head. I didn't want to believe i was taken for a fool as they seemed so friendly and knowledgeable. My thought " why would they want to screw over customers, especially in this economy? I'm sure this is how much everything costs." But the following day was time for me to do Grocery shopping and realized that my grocery store sells Sadaf brand spices which the Indian shop was proudly selling as one of their top brands. Naturally i added the prices of all the same spices and tea i bought at the indian shop including taxes to a sum of a little over $30?!?!?! I definitely feel ripped off tho. What makes this more peculiar was my visit prior to this. When i arrived at the shop the lady was happily explaining things to a couple of a customers, but I believe they were speaking in hindi so of course i didn't understand. But when they were checking out i noticed they were only walking out with one standard size supplement (that i had no knowledge about) bottle yet they were charged a very similar price to what i was charged my following visit. The customers were also surprised, but paid and walked off in the same disbelief.
They are friendly and very helpful, but be careful. Most of their items don't have labeled prices so question the price of everything prior to getting it to the register. They've caught onto the idea that people are much more willing to pay an obviously outrageous price while at the register (having had their emotions preyed on as they explain benefits and what not) rather than if they'd simply pick up the item and asked for the price.

I don't see how this tactic is worth it for them, anyone who walks out with any doubt on what they purchased will most likely just do a check on google for it. They certainly lost one customer.< /review>< UserId.>

< Text>
I take my employees to this restaurant every month to celebrate anniversaries.  Every single experience has been a great one- the staff are extremely attentive/responsive.  The owner- always concerned about providing a superior culinary experience.

An example- an employee thought something was too salty, so she didn't really touch her meal, but was uncomfortable about saying anything since she has little tolerance for salt.  When the owner saw it come back to the kitchen, he was genuinely concerned becuase she didn't tell him so that he could make her something else right away.

The crusts of the pizza are perfect- light, tender, with the lightest crisp.  The ingredients- clearly high quality.

We are NEVER rushed- the staff recognize a speedy lunch and the desire to lounge.  Great all around.< /Text>

< gmap_id>
0x80c33314b3dd2e31:0x2b25dcd666ed5d46< /gmap_id>
<Review>Black Bear Diner is worth a visit for the atmosphere. Everything, from the building and entry way, to the waiting area, to the dining spaces, to the bathroom is on theme. Even the waitstaff are decked out in bear paw suspenders (available for purchase at the register).
Outside of the atmosphere, the experience is average. The 50s-newspaper style menu is cute, but the service is a bit slow. The food is well portioned and not too expensive, but the quality is nothing to write home about. The waitstaff is responsive, but not affable.
The redeeming feature of my dining experience was the desserts: the huckleberry ice cream is original (and tasty!) and the blackberry cobbler was delicious.
Overall, Black Bear Diner is worth a visit  for the experience or a drop-in when you're in the area anyhow, but it won't be replacing my local favorites. The novelty of its atmosphere may wear off, but it's a solid diner.< /Review></record>

<Rating>3<//Rating><Text>Eek! I hate leaving a 3 star rating for good food. But bad service cannot be ignored.

When we arrived, a lady named Preslee seated us. Very unpleasant. No smiles.  Very cold. I was hoping she wasn't our server. She was. üò£

She comes back a minute later, took our drink order. We said we needed a minute. She didn't come back for like 10 minutes. The place wasn't that busy. One half was even closed off.

Took 27 minutes for our food to come out. When she brought it, my husband had to ask for a refill. And extra napkins. Took over 5 minutes. We asked for some mayonnaise when she brought that. We never got it.

Finally came back, and we asked for a box. After 5 minutes, my husband just went and got one at the counter. A few minutes later, we got the bill. SUPER dissapointed in our service.

That aside, the food is amazing. This was our first time at this location. We've been to the one in Klamath Falls, Or. And to the one in Rohnert Park, Ca many times.

The food is always amazing. This visit, I ordered the cheddar bacon burger, add avocado.  Well well done. It was a tad pink inside. The meat was super thick, but It was manageable. It was a darn good burger. Very flavorful. The fries were ok. Nothing special. Didn't have any salt.

Hubby got the chicken fried steak dinner. It was super good. Huge portions. he upgraded to a loaded baked potato. Yummy! He got mixed veggies, which he didn't eat, since he never got the mayo he asked for, to eat with them.

He got the cheddar broccoli soup with a cornbread muffin. Both were good. The soup was super creamy, and flavorful.

We will be back, although we will definetly avoid Preslee.< /Text>< Pictures>

Beverly Taylor< /username>
<Time>1553160313596< /Time>< rate>
5<//rate>
< Text>
Great regional chain diner! Excellent service. Cute, wonderfully kitschy bear motif throughout that makes me smile. I had a scramble, and there was a taco salad and a breakfast plate ordered at the table. Big Food. Excellent quality and delicious, so be not alarmed when you see massive plates on every table. Also feel free to ask for a box. They know how big their food is. They're cool about it. The service is friendly, attentive and prompt.

To anyone with food allergies, while they're not a specialized restaurant, the kitchen will work with you. I've developed a whole host of incredibly inconvenient food allergies (gluten, rice, peppers, potatoes, artificial dyes, most things that taste good...), and I was able to order a meal that was more than a salad without cobbling together twenty menu items. Our server made sure to note I have food sensitivities so I felt good about my meal prep without feeling like I was a pain... Wonderful! Thank you.

As a former diner dessert junkie, everything in the case looks like it's almost worth the misery (not quite) of the allergens inside... I can only imagine.<//Text>

< text>
Servings are humongous.

The sweet potato fries are to die for and their bacon ranch is very mildly baconed so really good.

The waffles are more like pancakes. Which are good but not your typical waffle.

The cornbread is heavenly.

The chicken fried steak melts in your mouth.

The Mac and cheese is pennie with a white cheese sauce. Could be cheesier.

Their breakfast ham is a half inch+ thick and fairly lean.< /text>

< text>
Tonight was the worst experience I have had at Black Bear Diner in Chino.
At 8 pm. and the restaurant about half full my wife and I waited over 10 minutes to get seated.
The entire time we waited there were six plates of food setting up on the counter.
There were 3 families in line to pay for their bill and 2 groups of 2 waiting to get seated.
I was told that there were no clean tables.
So 2 hours before they close there was no one to clean the tables, no one to take the money and no one to seat you.
After 10 minutes of waiting with no one else ahead of me someone came up and asking for my name to put me on the list to get seated.
All this time there were 5 people in the kitchen.
We walked out and went to Corky's and enjoyed our dinner.<//text>

< text>
This review is for a delivery order (thru Postmates) from this location..

Steak & Eggs were unexpectedly tasty.  They were cooked as requested & suprisingly delivered better than expected.

One egg with sausage & pancake was equally delicious.  I normally get bacon but glad I tried their sausage.  It's so good!

Black Bear Diner also uses really nice to-go containers so don't worry about spills or messes.

Great food, delivery & service.</text>

< Review>
I've been here twice now, once with my husband, this last time with a party of 4. Both times the food was great, but it took FOREVER! We went this past Sunday morning, got there about 8am and there was no wait. Restaurant wasn't packed yet, so we figured we would be good. We all ordered breakfast, and waited for 45 minutes for our food. Food was really good!! Biscuits and gravy could have used a little more gravy, but very yummy! Our waitress kept our coffee mugs full the whole time, which was great, but to wait that long for breakfast was excessive.
I would like to come back here, but I hope their food service picks up.< /Review>

<Rating>5< /Rating><Name>David Truong<//Name><resp>None</resp><Pics>None<//Pics>< review>
Pancakes! Yummy, yummy SWEET CREAM pancakes!

That's all you need to know. But just in case the wait scares you... let me just say it's worth it. I drove by for months before actually going in. But now that I've gone, I wish I would've gone sooner.

I came on a weekday morning and was seated immediately. I had no idea what to order, so my waitress pointed out the sweet cream pancakes are the winner. And she was right!! My mouth is watering just thinking about it.

We also ordered an omelet, chicken fried steak and a philly sandwich. Everything was made well and delivered quickly. Good service, friendly smiles, fair prices! I'll be back. Thanks BBD!< /review>

I walked in with my husband and this old man with his middle aged son are waiting with two other old men who were already there. The hostess asks us how many are in my party. I tell her two and this old man with a party of six which isn't even all together yet insists he be seated first so they can drink coffee. Okay. Fine. But the hostess never came back to seat us. We waited another 3 minutes for another server to come and seat us, which only happened because more customers had walked in already. <Name>rudey brain<//Name><date>1500263133241<//date><rate>1< /rate>< Review>
This place doesnt take reservations so we asked if they can accommodate a group of 20, which they said they easily could. They sat us immediately but things were downhill from there. The orders were wrong, the food was average, two orders were forgotten, and it took forever for simple things like refills, ketchup, etc. We realize it's a newer location for this chain and anticipated slower service but the food was disappointing as well as the customer service. The waiter tried very hard to do as much as he could but he literally had no help. The manager didnt come over until we requested her, even then she was very reluctant to offer support to the waiter. We've eaten at other Black Bear restaurants in Northern California but this location's service and especially food were VERY disappointing.< /Review>

<user_name>Burn Dup<//user_name>< Text>
Friends had hyped this place up pretty good, as they found it years before in far-Northern CA after emerging from the wilderness during a camping trip.

The theme is log-cabin-y, and the food is traditional "American Comfort Food" served in very large portions. Fortunately, they offer downsized (aka normal sized) portions of most of their dishes. I opted for this smaller serving of their meatloaf, as it was getting late in the evening.

It was good, it's hard to screw up meatloaf and mashed potatoes with gravy. The bacon beans tasted like they had sat in tupperware too many days after coming out of the can. Salad was food-service iceberg with generic food-service creamy blue cheese.

Where this place truly fell on it's face was service. Restaurant was at less than 25% capacity on a Tuesday evening, and it took over 30 minutes after ordering for our group of 7 to be served our meals. We were not an intimidating group, but the three waitresses working our particular dining room were scarce, and seemed to avoid our party, as if they thought we'd be extra work. So just as I was about to give up ordering a chocolate malt for dessert, I finally flagged a waitress down. 15 minutes later, I was served a ginormous, yet absolutely ordinary chocolate malt, when I should have been going to bed.

For a new place, the carpet had some gnarly stains, and the restroom was out of paper towels.

Their menu is a little newspaper-type thing. One "article" on the front page details the chain's absolutely cancerous growth in the last ten years, citing all of the diners they have opened up in various cities, with the rate of maliginancy exponentiating in the last two years.

Like any cancer, this growth will be soon fatal if they don't have proper management overseeing the twentysomethings that scurry around and crew this diner. Such management was clearly not present the evening of my visit.<//Text>
<time>1513197008645<//time>< response>
None<//response>
